    "narrative": "LawDog\u2019s lineup today is anchored by **Daulton Varsho** (69.94) and **Bryson Stott** (68.82), both of whom are set up for high-efficiency outings. **Daulton Varsho** benefits significantly from a favorable matchup against Bradley, and his dual-threat potential against a pitcher with a 4.45 xERA makes him our top play. Similarly, **Bryson Stott** enjoys a +13% platoon boost and a +4% park factor against Gallen. We are also leaning heavily into the top of the order; **Brendan Donovan** (68.26) and **Taylor Ward** (67.47) are strong starts, with **Brendan Donovan** taking advantage of a weak matchup against Bolton, while **Taylor Ward** thrives in a hitter-friendly park environment despite a slight platoon dip.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the card was keeping **Gleyber Torres** (53.93) on the bench. While his score is respectable, he ultimately fell short of the threshold required to displace our infield core, primarily due to a -13% platoon adjustment against Alcantara. We are also closely monitoring the status of **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (55.12). Facing an elite arm in Sale, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** carries significant risk; his score is suppressed by the matchup, but his pedigree and assumed #3 spot in the lineup keep him in the utility role. We must remain cautious with **Tyler Freeman** (55.49), who carries a 39% rain risk; if the weather deteriorates, we have depth ready to pivot to ensure we preserve our game caps.",
